parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ejection of a spark plug can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or fires.
The failure of the exhaust manifold can cause the vehicle to catch fire, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires can cause serious injuries or fatalities, as well as damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.

the brake pedal does not respond
and the engine RPM increases excessively.
